<paragraph blockId="10.[170,775,235,748]" pageId="10" pageNumber="3200">Morphometry: (length in mm). Male: Body 25.8, Tegmina 20.05, Hind femur 11.85, Pronotum 3.75. Female: Body 33.1, Tegmina 26.75, Hind femur 16.2, Pronotum 5.15.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[170,775,235,748]" pageId="10" pageNumber="3200">Remarks: Commonly found in vegetable fields of brinjal, lady finger, tomato and also in paddy fields.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[170,775,235,748]" pageId="10" pageNumber="3200">
Natural enemies: Red mite identified as 
<emphasis box="[170,453,609,635]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="3200">Eutrombidium trigonum</emphasis>
was found to infect the insect.
</paragraph>
